                                                                  What is Quality Analyst - QA?  


A quality analyst is responsible for testing the components and overall functionality of a product.

After the Developers develop the solution usually Quality Analyst will ensure that the solution is quality assured before being released to the customers.

The Quality Analyst usually will be running some tests and they will measure their testing against the business requirements.

The role of a quality analyst is involved throughout the initial, middle, and final stages of a product's development.

They validate test cases and oversee quality assurance in matters such as software usability and the overall SDLC (software development life cycle).

The quality Analyst job description includes accomplishing manual testing and then moving toward the automation part. They need to ensure that all the testing functionalities are working correctly.

The product is not eligible for release unless it has precisely met all quality requirements.
